🔹 What is Azure AD Connect?

It is a tool used to sync:

On-prem Active Directory (DC VM)
➡️ with
Azure AD (Microsoft Entra ID)
⚠️ Before Installation (Prerequisites)

Make sure these are ready:

✅ 1. Domain Controller VM
Windows Server (2016/2019/2022)
Active Directory installed

✅ 2. Azure AD Account
Global Admin access in Azure

✅ 3. Internet Access
DC VM must access internet

✅ 4. .NET Framework
Minimum .NET 4.7.1

🔹 Step 1: Download Tool
Open browser in your DC VM
Go to official site
Download Azure AD Connect

🔹 Step 2: Start Installation
Run the installer
Click I agree
Click Continue
🔹 Step 3: Choose Installation Type

👉 You will see two options:

✔️ Express Settings (Recommended for beginners)
Sync all users automatically
Minimal configuration

👉 Click Use Express Settings

🔹 Step 4: Connect Azure AD
Enter your Azure Global Admin credentials
🔹 Step 5: Connect On-Prem AD
Enter your Domain Admin credentials
🔹 Step 6: Configure Sync
It will auto-detect domain
Keep default settings (for learning/lab)

Click Next → Install

🔹 Step 7: Finish Installation
Installation will complete
Sync will start automatically
🔄 Step 8: Verify Sync
Go to Azure Portal
Open Microsoft Entra ID
Check Users

👉 Your on-prem users should appear there

🔧 Optional (Manual Sync Command)

If you want to force sync:

Open PowerShell:

Start-ADSyncSyncCycle -PolicyType Delta
